{
  "info": {
    "name": "Synthetic Data Generation API — v3.0",
    "description": "Synthetic Data Generation API — v3.0\n\n## Security\n- The Groq API key is configured **server-side only** via the `GROQ_API_KEY` env var.\n  It is never sent in any request body.\n- The `X-API-Key` header is optional. Enable it only if `API_SECRET_KEY` is set on the server.\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Start server: `python auto_pipeline.py --serve`\n2. Set `base_url` collection variable to `http://localhost:8000`\n3. Run **Health Check** — confirm `key_configured: true`\n4. Run **Save Connection** — register your DB under a name\n5. Run **Test Connection** — confirm DB is reachable\n6. Run **Run Pipeline (Async)** — job_id is saved automatically\n7. Run **Get Job Status** — poll until `status: completed`\n8. Run **Query Table** — browse generated data with pagination\n\n## New in v3\n- Data Viewer: paginated table browser with sort/filter\n- SQL Editor: execute DML/DDL/SELECT with dialect auto-detection\n- Import CSV: append or replace table data from a CSV file\n- Export: download data as DML INSERT statements, CSV, or DDL\n- Connection Manager: save and switch between multiple DB connections",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": "3.0.0"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "job_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated by Run Pipeline (Async) test script"
    },
    {
      "key": "connection_name",
      "value": "DatagenDB",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Name of the saved connection to use for data viewer / SQL editor"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_secret_key",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Set this only if the server has API_SECRET_KEY configured. Leave blank for local dev."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "System",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Check API health, version info, and whether the Groq API key is configured on the server.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\",\n  \"version\": \"2.1.0\",\n  \"key_configured\": true,\n  \"supported_engines\": [\"postgres\", \"oracle\", \"sqlserver\", \"mysql\"]\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Connection Manager",
      "description": "Save, list, and delete named database connections.\nConnections are stored server-side and referenced by name in all Data Viewer, SQL Editor, Import, and Export requests.\n\nWorkflow:\n1. POST /data/connections — save a connection (tests it first)\n2. GET  /data/connections — list all saved connections\n3. DELETE /data/connections/{name} — remove a connection",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Connections",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections"]
            },
            "description": "List all saved database connections. Passwords are never returned.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"connections\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"DatagenDB\",\n      \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n      \"host\": \"localhost\",\n      \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n      \"schema\": \"banking\",\n      \"_has_password\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Save Connection — PostgreSQL",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var response = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (response.success && response.connection) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('connection_name', response.connection.name);",
                  "  console.log('Connection saved:', response.connection.name);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"DatagenDB\",\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 5432,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"postgres\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"banking\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections"]
            },
            "description": "Save a named PostgreSQL connection. The server tests connectivity before saving.\nThe connection name is auto-saved to the `connection_name` collection variable.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"connection\": {\n    \"name\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\"\n  }\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Save Connection — Oracle",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"OracleDB\",\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"oracle\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 1521,\n    \"service_name\": \"ORCL\",\n    \"dbname\": \"ORCL\",\n    \"user\": \"banking_user\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"BANKING\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections"]
            },
            "description": "Save a named Oracle connection."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Save Connection — SQL Server",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"SQLServerDB\",\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"sqlserver\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 1433,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"sa\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"dbo\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections"]
            },
            "description": "Save a named SQL Server connection."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Save Connection — MySQL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"MySQLDB\",\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"mysql\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 3306,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"root\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"DatagenDB\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections"]
            },
            "description": "Save a named MySQL connection."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Connection",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/connections/{{connection_name}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "connections", "{{connection_name}}"]
            },
            "description": "Remove a saved connection by name.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\"success\": true, \"deleted\": \"DatagenDB\"}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Schema",
      "description": "Test connectivity and read schema metadata without generating data.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Test Connection — PostgreSQL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 5432,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"postgres\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"banking\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/schema/test-connection",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "schema", "test-connection"]
            },
            "description": "Test PostgreSQL connection without saving it."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test Connection — Oracle",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"oracle\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 1521,\n    \"service_name\": \"ORCL\",\n    \"dbname\": \"ORCL\",\n    \"user\": \"system\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"BANKING\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/schema/test-connection",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "schema", "test-connection"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test Connection — SQL Server",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"sqlserver\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 1433,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"sa\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"dbo\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/schema/test-connection",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "schema", "test-connection"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Test Connection — MySQL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"mysql\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 3306,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"root\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"DatagenDB\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/schema/test-connection",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "schema", "test-connection"]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Read Schema",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"database\": {\n    \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n    \"host\": \"localhost\",\n    \"port\": 5432,\n    \"dbname\": \"DatagenDB\",\n    \"user\": \"postgres\",\n    \"password\": \"yourpassword\",\n    \"schema\": \"banking\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/schema/read",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "schema", "read"]
            },
            "description": "Read schema metadata (tables, columns, PKs, FKs) without generating data."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Data Viewer",
      "description": "Browse and query table data after generation.\nAll endpoints require a `connection_name` that was previously saved via POST /data/connections.\n\nTypical workflow:\n1. GET  /data/tables         — list tables in schema\n2. GET  /data/preview/{tbl}  — quick 100-row preview\n3. POST /data/query          — paginated view with sort + filter\n4. POST /data/count          — get row count",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Tables",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/tables?connection_name={{connection_name}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "tables"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "connection_name",
                  "value": "{{connection_name}}",
                  "description": "Name of a previously saved connection"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List all tables in the schema for a saved connection.\nReturns table names, column counts, and primary key columns.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"connection\": \"DatagenDB\",\n  \"schema\": \"banking\",\n  \"engine\": \"postgres\",\n  \"tables\": [\n    {\"name\": \"tstg_customer\", \"column_count\": 12, \"primary_keys\": [\"CUSTOMER_NO\"]},\n    {\"name\": \"tstg_account\",  \"column_count\": 18, \"primary_keys\": [\"ACCOUNT_NO\"]}\n  ]\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Preview Table (first 100 rows)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/preview/tstg_aa_accountdetail?connection_name={{connection_name}}&limit=100",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "preview", "tstg_aa_accountdetail"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "connection_name",
                  "value": "{{connection_name}}"
                },
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "100",
                  "description": "Number of rows to return (max 1000)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Quick preview — returns the first N rows of a table without pagination.\nUsed by the UI to show data immediately after selecting a table.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\",\n  \"columns\": [\"ARRANGEMENT_ID\", \"VALUE_DATE\", \"START_DATE\", ...],\n  \"rows\": [[\"AA2406A0001\", \"2024-11-17\", \"2024-11-17\", ...]]\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Query Table (paginated)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\",\n  \"page\": 1,\n  \"page_size\": 100,\n  \"order_by\": \"ARRANGEMENT_ID\",\n  \"order_dir\": \"ASC\",\n  \"filters\": {}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/query",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "query"]
            },
            "description": "Paginated, sortable, filterable table data viewer.\n\nRequest fields:\n- `connection_name`: saved connection name\n- `table`: table name\n- `page`: page number (1-based)\n- `page_size`: rows per page (max 1000)\n- `order_by`: column name to sort by (optional)\n- `order_dir`: ASC or DESC\n- `filters`: {\"column_name\": \"value\"} for equality filters (optional)\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"connection\": \"DatagenDB\",\n  \"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\",\n  \"columns\": [\"ARRANGEMENT_ID\", \"VALUE_DATE\", ...],\n  \"column_meta\": {\n    \"ARRANGEMENT_ID\": {\"data_type\": \"varchar\", \"is_pk\": true, \"is_nullable\": false}\n  },\n  \"rows\": [[\"AA2406A0001\", \"2024-11-17\", ...]],\n  \"page\": 1,\n  \"page_size\": 100,\n  \"total\": 300,\n  \"total_pages\": 3,\n  \"engine\": \"postgres\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Query Table (with filter)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\",\n  \"page\": 1,\n  \"page_size\": 50,\n  \"order_by\": \"VALUE_DATE\",\n  \"order_dir\": \"DESC\",\n  \"filters\": {\n    \"CURRENCY\": \"USD\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/query",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "query"]
            },
            "description": "Example query with a filter applied — returns only rows where CURRENCY = 'USD', sorted by VALUE_DATE descending."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Count Rows",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\",\n  \"filters\": {}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/data/count",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "data", "count"]
            },
            "description": "Return the row count for a table with optional filter.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\"table\": \"tstg_aa_accountdetail\", \"count\": 300}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "SQL Editor",
      "description": "Execute SQL directly against a saved connection.\nThe dialect endpoint tells the UI which language mode to use in the code editor (Monaco/CodeMirror).\n\nDialect values returned:\n  postgres   → pgsql\n  oracle     → plsql\n  sqlserver  → tsql\n  mysql      → mysql\n\nWorkflow:\n1. GET  /sql/dialect  — configure editor language mode\n2. POST /sql/execute  — run a query, DML, or DDL\n3. GET  /sql/history  — see previous statements",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get SQL Dialect (for editor config)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/dialect?connection_name={{connection_name}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "dialect"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "connection_name",
                  "value": "{{connection_name}}",
                  "description": "Name of a previously saved connection"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns SQL dialect info for a saved connection.\nThe frontend uses this to set the Monaco / CodeMirror editor language mode automatically.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"dialect\":     \"pgsql\",\n  \"label\":       \"PostgreSQL\",\n  \"placeholder\": \"%s\",\n  \"engine\":      \"postgres\",\n  \"schema\":      \"banking\"\n}\n```\n\nDialect values:\n- postgres   → `pgsql`\n- oracle     → `plsql`\n- sqlserver  → `tsql`\n- mysql      → `mysql`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute SELECT",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT * FROM \\\"banking\\\".\\\"tstg_aa_accountdetail\\\" LIMIT 50\",\n  \"max_rows\": 1000\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Execute any SELECT statement. Returns columns + rows as JSON.\nErrors are returned in the response body (not as HTTP 500) so the SQL editor can display them inline.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"columns\": [\"ARRANGEMENT_ID\", \"VALUE_DATE\", ...],\n  \"rows\": [[\"AA2406A0001\", \"2024-11-17\", ...]],\n  \"row_count\": 50,\n  \"statement_type\": \"SELECT\",\n  \"truncated\": false,\n  \"execution_ms\": 24.5,\n  \"dialect\": {\"dialect\": \"pgsql\", \"label\": \"PostgreSQL\"},\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute SELECT — Oracle",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"OracleDB\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT * FROM \\\"BANKING\\\".\\\"TSTG_AA_ACCOUNTDETAIL\\\" WHERE ROWNUM <= 50\",\n  \"max_rows\": 1000\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Execute a SELECT against Oracle. Note the Oracle-style ROWNUM pagination and uppercase table names."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute SELECT — SQL Server",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"SQLServerDB\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT TOP 50 * FROM [dbo].[tstg_aa_accountdetail]\",\n  \"max_rows\": 1000\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Execute a SELECT against SQL Server. Note the T-SQL TOP syntax and bracket quoting."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute SELECT — MySQL",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"MySQLDB\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT * FROM `DatagenDB`.`tstg_aa_accountdetail` LIMIT 50\",\n  \"max_rows\": 1000\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Execute a SELECT against MySQL. Note the backtick quoting."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute DML (INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"sql\": \"UPDATE \\\"banking\\\".\\\"tstg_aa_accountdetail\\\" SET \\\"RENEWAL_DATE\\\" = '2026-01-01' WHERE \\\"ARRANGEMENT_ID\\\" = 'AA2406A0001'\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Execute an UPDATE, INSERT, or DELETE statement.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"columns\": [],\n  \"rows\": [],\n  \"row_count\": 1,\n  \"statement_type\": \"DML\",\n  \"execution_ms\": 12.1,\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Execute DDL (CREATE / ALTER / DROP)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"sql\": \"CREATE INDEX idx_arrangement_currency ON \\\"banking\\\".\\\"tstg_aa_accountdetail\\\" (\\\"CURRENCY\\\")\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/ddl",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "ddl"]
            },
            "description": "Execute a DDL statement (CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE).\nThis is a separate endpoint from /execute so the UI can show a confirmation dialog before calling it.\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\"columns\": [], \"rows\": [], \"row_count\": 0, \"statement_type\": \"DDL\", \"error\": null}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Explain Query",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT * FROM \\\"banking\\\".\\\"tstg_aa_accountdetail\\\" WHERE \\\"CURRENCY\\\" = 'USD'\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/explain",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "explain"]
            },
            "description": "Return the query execution plan.\nEngine-aware:\n- PostgreSQL → EXPLAIN ANALYZE\n- Oracle     → EXPLAIN PLAN FOR\n- MySQL      → EXPLAIN\n- SQL Server → Returns guidance to use SET SHOWPLAN_TEXT ON in the editor\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"explain_rows\": [[\"Seq Scan on tstg_aa_accountdetail (cost=0.00..8.50 rows=1)\"]],\n  \"columns\": [\"QUERY PLAN\"],\n  \"error\": null\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate SQL (syntax check)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"connection_name\": \"{{connection_name}}\",\n  \"sql\": \"SELECT * FRUM \\\"banking\\\".\\\"tstg_aa_accountdetail\\\"\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/validate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Validate SQL syntax without executing or modifying any data.\nRuns EXPLAIN only — safe to call on every keystroke with debounce.\n\nExpected response (invalid SQL):\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"error\": \"syntax error at or near \\\"FRUM\\\"\"\n}\n```\n\nExpected response (valid SQL):\n```json\n{\"valid\": true, \"error\": null}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Query History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/sql/history?connection_name={{connection_name}}&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "sql", "history"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "connection_name", "value": "{{connection_name}}"},
                {"key": "limit", "value": "20", "description": "Number of recent queries to return"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "Return the last N SQL statements executed for a connection (in-memory, resets on server restart).\n\nExpected response:\n```json\n{\n  \"connection\": \"DatagenDB\",\n  \"history\": [\n    {\n      \"sql\": \"SELECT * FROM ...\",\n      \"executed_at\": \"2026-04-20T14:24:05\",\n      \"statement_type\": \"SELECT\",\n      \"row_count\": 50,\n      \"error\": null\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
